        "# Biometric Identification System Simulation\n",
        "This model takes a fingerprint as input and processes it using the algorithm SIFT to convert it into comparable data. It then compares the fingerprint to a number of fingerprints in a database using a brute force matcher and returns the best match. A user can then be identified and some of their personal data can be retrieved. In other words, this model simulates the process of how biometric systems in the real world use fingerprint data in order to identify individuals."
